📍Matheran 🌧️☔ Travel with THRILLOFEEL 😍 Departure Date (From Ahmedabad/ Vadodara/ Surat): ⬇️ 👉 June: 5, 12, 19, 26 👉 July: 3, 10, 17, 24, 31 👉 August: 07(Rakshabandhan), 14(independence day & Satam Atham), 21, 28 👉 September : 4, 11, 18, 25 Some Attractions of Matheran:- ⬇️ ✅ Heritage toy train 🚂 🚆 ✅ Garbett plateau trek ✅ Waterfall (reverse waterfall if heavy Wind)🍃 ✅ Matheran Market Visit ✅ Panorama Point/ Echo Point ✅ Motor Vehicle free hill station ------ Matheran Trip Itinerary: 👉 Day 0: Overnight Journey from Ahmedabad/ Vadodara/ Surat/ Mumbai by Train 🚂/ By Bus 🚐 👉 Day 1: - Reach at Mumbai in Morning & way to matheran by taxi - Breakfast On the way - Reach Matheran - Reach resort at matheran - Check in, Freshen Up, Lunch - Take a dive in Swimming Pool - Matheran Sight scene circuit Eco Point, Charlotte Lake, Edward Point, Waterfall (Revert Waterfall during rain) - Matheran Market 👉 Day 2: - Early Breakfast - Garbett Plateau Trek/Peb Fort Trek (5-6 hours) - Late Lunch at Hotel - Free time to Rest, explore around, swimming pool, nearby view point - Dinner - Music, Garba , Group activities - Night Walk/Jungle Hike to nearby view point* 👉 Day 3: - Morning Breakfast and Check out from Hotel - Experience *Heritage Toy Train* (3Km ride)* on self - Reach to Matheran Parking - Toy Train Trek* till Ganesh Statues of matheran/Kadyavarch Ganpati carved from single boulder (Trek 4Km easy walk)* - Reach neral by 3 pm & Drop at Mumbai 06:45PM - Return Journey by Train 👉 Day 4: - Reach Ahmedabad in the morning Overall Itinerary will remain flexible depending on weather conditions and group interest. #matheran #matherantrip #matheranhills #hillstation #near #mumbai #maharashtra #package #from #ahmedabad #vadodara #surat #fyp #travelwiththrillofeel #feelthethrill #thrillofeel

🤤🍫Chocolate mochi with Crispy Coating Recipe Chocolate Sauce: Dark Chocolate 100g Hot Whipping Cream (70°C) 100g Daifuku Skin: Glutinous Rice Flour 100g Cornstarch 30g Granulated Sugar 30g Cocoa Powder 10g Milk 180g Butter 15g Whipping Cream 250g Glaze: Dark Chocolate 100g Coconut Oil 30g Crushed Peanuts 30g 1 Stir the dark chocolate and 70°C hot cream until well combined, then refrigerate to set. 2 To make the mochi skin, add glutinous rice flour, cornstarch, sugar, cocoa powder, and milk into a mixing bowl. Stir well, then sift through a fine mesh. Cover with plastic wrap, poke a few holes, and steam for 30 minutes. After steaming, add butter while still hot, knead well, and stretch repeatedly until the dough is elastic. 3 Whip the filling cream by combining heavy cream and cooled chocolate sauce. Whip to 90% stiff peaks. 4 Divide the dough into 35g portions. Dust with toasted flour to prevent sticking, then roll out into skins. Place them into molds, add a layer of cream, followed by chocolate crisp pearls, then another layer of cream. Wrap up and freeze for later use. 5 To make the chocolate glaze, combine dark chocolate and coconut oil in a bowl and melt over a double boiler. Add crushed peanuts and stir until evenly mixed. Cool to 35°C, then pour over the mochi. #mochi #qelegcake#chocolate#softpastry#recipe #yummy #satisfying #snack #baking #foodphotography #foodphotographyandstyling #foodgasm #tasty #dessert #inspiration #instagood #cakeart #sugarart #cakeideas #LoveCelebration #BeautifulMoments #baking#share#sharefood#asmrfood

Palha italiana de oreo com 🍫 Ingredientes: 1 leite condensado (395g) 1 creme de leite (200g) 3 colheres (sopa) leite em pó 1 pacote de oreo 250g chocolate meio amargo Para o brigadeiro leve todos os ingredientes para o fogo médio e fique mexendo até desgrudar do fundo da panela. Depois acrescente as bolachas picadas misture e coloque sobre um recipiente com plástico de cozinha aberto. Deixe bem fechadinho e leve para o congelador por pelo menos 4horas. Para a cobertura derreta o chocolate de 30 em 30 segundos no microondas. Eu adicione 2 colheres de sopa de óleo de coco sem sabor para a casquinha ficar mais fina, mas é opcional. Desenforme a palha italiana, corte em quadradinhos e passe no chocolate derretido. Leve pra geladeira uns minutos pra secar e está pronto

FULL RECIPE for the BEST summer treat ☀️🍨 Oreo Ice Cream Sandwiches Ingredients: • 600g Oreo cookies (~50 cookies) • 170g unsalted butter, melted • 500g heavy cream • 1 tbsp vanilla extract • 150g condensed milk Instructions: 1. Line a 9x9” pan with parchment paper. 2. Blitz Oreos into fine crumbs (or crush in a Ziploc with a rolling pin). 3. Set aside 100g of crumbs. 4. Mix the remaining crumbs with melted butter. 5. Press half the crumb mixture into the pan to form a crust. Freeze. 6. Beat heavy cream and vanilla to stiff peaks. Fold in condensed milk, then the reserved Oreo crumbs. 7. Pour filling over the crust and smooth. Freeze 1–2 hours until firm. 8. Top with remaining crumbs, gently pressing down. Freeze 6+ hours or overnight. 9. Lift out, slice into 8 sandwiches with a hot knife. 10. Serve immediately or store in the freezer.
